Class Book

java.lang.Object
com.example.cab302assessment10b0101.model.Book
public class Book extends Object
The Book class represents a book entity in the library management system. It includes properties such as book ID, collection ID, title, ISBN, author, description, publication date, publisher, pages, notes, and an image representing the book cover.

  • Method Details

    • getPublicationDateAsLocalDate

      public LocalDate getPublicationDateAsLocalDate()
      Converts the publication date from a String to a LocalDate.

      This method attempts to parse the publication date using multiple date formats:

      • MM-dd-yyyy (e.g., 08-09-2015)
      • yyyy-MM-dd (e.g., 2024-10-07)
      • yyyy-MM-d (e.g., 2024-10-7)
      If the string doesn't match any of these formats, it returns null.
      Returns:
      the publication date as a LocalDate, or null if the date is not formatted correctly.
      Throws:
      DateTimeParseException - if none of the formats match the string representation of the date.
